 Starten überschrieben/gesetzt werden, genauso wie Volumes hier gemappt werden können oder auch Ports:\n\n\\begin{listing}[H]\n\t\\begin{codeblock}{sh}\npodman run docker.io/library/nginx:alpine echo "hello"\n# hello\n# (container exits after successfully running that command)\n\t\\end{codeblock}\n\t\\begin{codeblock}{sh}\npodman run -p 3000:80 \\\n           -v ./public:/usr/share/nginx/html:Z \\\n           docker.io/library/nginx:alpine\n# starts webserver on Host port 3000\n# maps static HTML directory to local ./public directory\n\t\\end{codeblock}\n\t\\caption{Befehle zum Starten eines Containers bei denen der Startbefehl, Port oder Volume gesetzt werden können}\n\\end{listing}'}], 'model': 'unsloth/gemma-4-E4B-it-GGUF:UD-Q3_K_XL', 'temperature': 0.7, 'tools': [{'type': 'function', 'function': {'name': 'tool_list_files', 'description': 'List all files of this LaTeX project with access', 'parameters': {'type': 'object', 'properties': {}, 'required': []}}}, {'type': 'function', 'function': {'name': 'tool_read_file', 'description': 'Read a file (returns error if no permission)', 'parameters': {'type': 'object', 'properties': {'file_path': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['file_path']}}}, {'type': 'function', 'function': {'name': 'tool_write_file', 'description': 'Write a file (returns error if no permission)', 'parameters': {'type': 'object', 'properties': {'file_path': {'type': 'string'}, 'content': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['file_path', 'content']}}}, {'type': 'function', 'function': {'name': 'tool_delegate_file_check', 'description': 'Delegate the file check to another agent given the file path and a crafted prompt for the agent', 'parameters': {'type': 'object', 'properties': {'file': {'type': 'string'}, 'prompt': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['file', 'prompt']}}}]}}
